Public Domain Dedication for Text Content
=========================================

The historical Chinese text content in this repository — under
`texts/`, `annotations/`, `variants/`, and the body of source HTML
snapshots in `sources/` — is in the public domain.

Specifically:

  - 《三國志》(Sanguozhi) was written by 陳壽 (Chen Shou, 233–297 CE).
  - 裴松之 (Pei Songzhi, 372–451 CE) compiled the supplementary 注
    (annotations) cited under 〈...〉 brackets and stored under
    `annotations/`.

Both works have been in the public domain worldwide for well over a
thousand years, far exceeding any copyright term that has ever existed.

