Source attribution (informational)
----------------------------------

While not legally required given the public-domain status of the text,
you are encouraged to credit upstream sources when redistributing:

  - Canonical text: zh.wikisource.org (per-page URLs recorded in
    each text file's `source.url` frontmatter field).
  - Variant comparison: ctext.org (per-page URLs recorded in
    `variants/.../sources/ctext.url`).

The HTML snapshots under `sources/wikisource/` and `sources/ctext/`
were retrieved as-is from those sites and are kept here for
reproducibility (every parse step can be re-run offline against them).
The textual content within the snapshots is, as above, public domain.
